  "text": "Subcutaneous fat thickness differed between Control bulls and both groups of steers at the end of the steers' housing period (P<0.001) (Table 3 ) but did not differ thereafter. The greater subcutaneous fat thickness of Control bulls compared with TMR and Gsupp steers was related to differences in LW as both variables were highly correlated (r=0.71, P<0.001). Moreover, concentrate feeding usually enhances fat deposition compared with forage feeding [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It would have been expected that TMR and G-supp steers had different subcutaneous fat thickness measured by ultrasonography because fatness differed in the commercial and 10 th rib dissection. Nevertheless, ultrasonography was unable to detect differences in fat deposition between TMR and G-supp steers.",
